    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Heliocoprion",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Though not a true shark, the helicoprion belongs to a similar lineage of cartilaginous fishes. The predator's most striking feature is its tooth whorls, which spiral outward in its lower jaw.",
